---
description: Testing — Vitest, RTL, Playwright where and how to add tests
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use the test stack from AGENTS.md (e.g. Vitest, React Testing Library for components).
- Where: Unit tests for services and utilities; React Testing Library for components.
- Each new component must include at least one test file in the same folder, named like the component with `.test.tsx` extension.
- Never mock unnecessarily; only mock when needed (e.g. network requests).
- Add only the minimum necessary tests.
- Do not add very simple smoke tests.
- Logics should cover helper functions so regressions stay obvious.
- Hooks reacting to async data must be mocked/tested for loading, success, and error states.
- RTL component tests must assert rendered elements and user interactions for all key flows.
- Form submission tests verify callbacks receive the correct payload and error states show expected messages.
- Always cover view states (loading, empty, error) so UI feedback stays consistent.
- Components should update correctly when their critical props or data change.
- Minimal validation checks go in Vitest only if no other validator tool covers them (block submit/show message for invalid input).
